
---- To determine a system's platform ---------

  1. Exit the Solaris installation program.
  
  2. Type the uname -mp command at the root 
     prompt. 

     NOTE: The uname -mp command displays
     the platform group, followed by 
     the processor type.

     For example:

     Solaris Power PC    prep ppc
     SPARC               sun4 sparc
     x86                i86pc i386
         
  3. Restart the Solaris installation program.

